solution: By the distributive property, we can rewrite this as: $$16\left (\frac{125}{2}+\frac{25}{4}+\frac{9}{16}+1\right) =16\left (\frac{125}{2}\right)+16\left (\frac{25}{4}\right )+16\left (\frac{9}{16} \right) +16$$$$=8\cdot 125+4\cdot 25+9+16=1000+100+9+16=\boxed{1125}.$$
model_solution:
Step 1: Multiply 16 by the expression inside the parentheses: $16\left (\frac{125}{2}+\frac{25}{4}+\frac{9}{16}+1\right) = 16 \times \left (\frac{125}{2}+\frac{25}{4}+\frac{9}{16}+1\right)$.
Step 2: $16 \times \left (\frac{125}{2}+\frac{25}{4}+\frac{9}{16}+1\right) = 8 \times 125 + 4 \times 25 + 16 \times \frac{9}{16} + 16$
$8 \times 125 + 4 \times 25 + 16 \times \frac{9}{16} + 16 = 1000 + 100 + 9 + 16 = 1125$
Final Answer: $\boxed{1125}$
